Class AppInBackgroundStateMonitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.device.utilities.AppInBackgroundStateMonitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.app.Application.ActivityLifecycleCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2

    public class AppInBackgroundStateMonitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.app.Application.ActivityLifecycleCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2
    This class notifies it's clients about situation when application is in background state.

      • onTrimMemory

        public void onTrimMemory(int level)
        This method is called when app should trim memory. One of the reasons why it is called is that app went in background. In such a case level == ComponentCallbacks2.TRIM_MEMORY_UI_HIDDEN. We are waiting for such a case and notifying listeners them.
        Specified by:
        onTrimMemory in interface android.content.ComponentCallbacks2
        Parameters:
        level - trim memory level
